    <div class="accordion">
      
      				<div class="accordion-item open">
				  <div class="accordion-title">What is AIX BOND?<span class="arrow">-</span></div>
				  <div class="accordion-content" style="display: block;">
					<p>AIX Bond is a fixed income BOND, where the underlying asset management strategies yield a fixed annual income paid at a quarterly frequency.</p>
				  </div>
			  	</div>
							<div class="accordion-item ">
				  <div class="accordion-title">Are my returns subject to change, depending on the Market conditions or guaranteed?<span class="arrow">+</span></div>
				  <div class="accordion-content" >
					<p>The returns paid in the form of Coupon rates for the AIX BOND are fixed returns, irrespective of market conditions.</p>
				  </div>
			  	</div>
							<div class="accordion-item ">
				  <div class="accordion-title">What is the term of Investment?<span class="arrow">+</span></div>
				  <div class="accordion-content" >
					<p>The term of investment for subscribing for the AIX BOND is a fixed period from the issuance date. Depending on the subscription date, the remaining tenure would be the term of the Investment.</p>
				  </div>
			  	</div>
							<div class="accordion-item ">
				  <div class="accordion-title">Is the BOND resalable in the Secondary market?<span class="arrow">+</span></div>
				  <div class="accordion-content" >
					<p>There is no Secondary market or liquidity provided by the Issuer but the BOND can be freely transferred to a third party under a private agreement.</p>
				  </div>
			  	</div>
							<div class="accordion-item ">
				  <div class="accordion-title">Who is issuing the BOND?<span class="arrow">+</span></div>
				  <div class="accordion-content" >
					<p>The BONDS are issued by a Special Purpose Vehicle (SPV) incorporated in Ireland whose sole purpose is to issue the said Notes under its approved Program. The SPV is a multi issuance vehicle designed to issue segregated Series of Notes. It can also be referred to as a Ã¢â‚¬Å“Securitization VehicleÃ¢â‚¬Â.</p>
				  </div>
			  	</div>
							<div class="accordion-item ">
				  <div class="accordion-title">Can I purchase the bond in other currencies?<span class="arrow">+</span></div>
				  <div class="accordion-content" >
					<p>Yes. Equivalent structures are available in EUR and CHF, each issued under a separate ISIN, providing investors with currency flexibility.</p>
				  </div>
			  	</div>
